%Color Themes 
%"A color theme only dictates which colors are used in a presentation. If you have chosen a particular presentation theme and then choose a color theme, only the colors of your presentation will change. A color theme can specify colors in a very detailed way: For example, a color theme can specifically change the colors used to render, say, the border of a button, the background of a button, and the text on a button." Beamer User Guide sec. 15.1

% Required packages
\RequirePackage{xcolor}

% Defines the Nordling Lab colors
% Note that xcolor with the (default) natural option does not do any colour space conversions, and you have access to the PDF "DeviceRGB", "DeviceCMYK" and "DeviceGray" spaces.
% Colors defined in cmyk (preferred because they closely match the RGB values in Mac's Digital Color Meter (Display native values) in TNL_final-logo.pdf and TNL_PPT_selected.pdf)
\definecolor{NLblack}{cmyk}{0,0,0,1} %Used in black logo
\definecolor{NLlightblue}{cmyk}{0.7,0.12,0.17,0} %Used in one color light blue logo and official two color logo %Corresponds to R70, G164, B182 in Mac's Digital Color Meter (Display native values)
\definecolor{NLmiddleblue}{cmyk}{0.79,0.27,0.15,0} %Used in middle of presentation title page banner %Corresponds to R44, G139, B169 in Mac's Digital Color Meter (Display native values)
\definecolor{NLdarkblue}{cmyk}{0.93,0.58,0.37,0.16} %Used in official two color logo %Corresponds to R33, G82, B101 in Mac's Digital Color Meter (Display native values)
\definecolor{NLlightgrey}{cmyk}{0,0,0,.3} %Used in official greyscale logo
\definecolor{NLdarkgrey}{cmyk}{0,0,0,.85} %Used in official greyscale logo

% Defines the same elements as found in the Beamer color theme Albatross
\setbeamercolor*{normal text}{fg=black,bg=white} %Same as default theme

\DeclareOption{overlystylish}
{
  \def\beamer@cta@do{
    \setbeamertemplate{background canvas}[vertical shading][bottom=NLlightblue,top=NLlightblue,middle=white!75!NLlightblue]
  }
}
\ProcessOptions

\@ifundefined{beamer@cta@do}{}{\beamer@cta@do}

\mode<presentation>

\setbeamercolor*{alerted text}{fg=NLdarkblue}
\setbeamercolor*{example text}{fg=NLlightblue}
\setbeamercolor*{structure}{fg=black}

% Black to grey palette
